  "prompt": "How can I change the \"Ok Google\" phrase to something else in a Nexus 6?",
  "response": "You can't officially change the \"Ok Google\" or \"Hey Google\" wake phrase to something else on Android devices, including the Nexus 6. This is a built-in feature of Google's voice assistant, and Google does not provide an option to customize the wake word.\n\nHowever, if you are comfortable with third-party apps and rooting your device, there may be alternative solutions, although they come with risks:\n\n1. **Root Your Device**: This process gives you superuser access to your device, but it voids warranties and can make your phone vulnerable to security risks.\n\n2. **Third-Party Apps**: Some third-party apps claim to allow the customization of the wake word. These apps may require root access and can be unstable or unreliable.\n\n3. **Tasker and AutoVoice**: These apps, especially when used together, can create custom voice commands. Tasker automates tasks based on certain triggers, and AutoVoice integrates with Tasker to handle custom voice commands. However, this won't change the wake word for Google Assistant; rather, it allows you to create custom voice interactions after using the standard wake word.\n\nProceed with these steps only if you're comfortable with technical modifications and understand the potential risks, including data loss and security vulnerabilities. Always back up your device and ensure you understand the implications of rooting or installing third-party apps.",
